    {
      "text": "What is the major concern associated with bupivacaine toxicity?",
      "options": [
        {
          "label": "A",
          "text": "Liver toxicity",
          "correct": false
        },
        {
          "label": "B",
          "text": "Nephrotoxicity",
          "correct": false
        },
        {
          "label": "C",
          "text": "Cardiotoxicity",
          "correct": true
        },
        {
          "label": "D",
          "text": "Neurotoxicity",
          "correct": false
        }
      ],
      "correct_answer": "C. Cardiotoxicity",
      "question_images": [],
      "explanation_images": [],
      "explanation": "<table cellspacing=\"0\" style=\"border-collapse:collapse; width:624px\">\n<tbody>\n<tr>\n<td style=\"border-bottom:1px solid #000000; border-left:1px solid #000000; border-right:1px solid #000000; border-top:1px solid #000000; vertical-align:top\">\n<p><strong>Classification</strong></p>\n</td>\n<td style=\"border-bottom:1px solid #000000; border-left:1px solid #000000; border-right:1px solid #000000; border-top:1px solid #000000; vertical-align:top\">\n<ul>\n<li>Bupivacaine is an amide-type local anesthetic</li>\n</ul>\n</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td style=\"border-bottom:1px solid #000000; border-left:1px solid #000000; border-right:1px solid #000000; border-top:1px solid #000000; vertical-align:top\">\n<p><strong>Mechanism of Action </strong></p>\n</td>\n<td style=\"border-bottom:1px solid #000000; border-left:1px solid #000000; border-right:1px solid #000000; border-top:1px solid #000000; vertical-align:top\">\n<ul>\n<li>It works by <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"9dc12b322016927771830dff673eeb\">blocking</span> sodium channels in nerve membranes, preventing the <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"bface068bb16927771964819228c66\">propagation</span> of nerve impulses, which results in local anesthesia.</li>\n</ul>\n</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td style=\"border-bottom:1px solid #000000; border-left:1px solid #000000; border-right:1px solid #000000; border-top:1px solid #000000; vertical-align:top\">\n<p><strong>Clinical Uses </strong></p>\n</td>\n<td style=\"border-bottom:1px solid #000000; border-left:1px solid #000000; border-right:1px solid #000000; border-top:1px solid #000000; vertical-align:top\">\n<ul>\n<li>Commonly used for spinal, epidural, and <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"255674f3271692777195c172d86daf\">peripheral</span> nerve blocks.</li>\n<li>Widely used in labor and delivery for <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"6de01005f61692777187a3003970c7\">epidural</span> <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"e24b7bd55d16927771818aaa6ad0ed\">anesthesia</span> and in long-duration surgeries.</li>\n</ul>\n</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td style=\"border-bottom:1px solid #000000; border-left:1px solid #000000; border-right:1px solid #000000; border-top:1px solid #000000; vertical-align:top\">\n<p><strong>Duration of Action</strong></p>\n</td>\n<td style=\"border-bottom:1px solid #000000; border-left:1px solid #000000; border-right:1px solid #000000; border-top:1px solid #000000; vertical-align:top\">\n<ul>\n<li>Longer duration of action compared to other local anesthetics like lidocaine. It can provide <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"e24b7bd55d16927771818aaa6ad0ed\">anesthesia</span> for several hours, making it ideal for prolonged procedures.</li>\n</ul>\n</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td style=\"border-bottom:1px solid #000000; border-left:1px solid #000000; border-right:1px solid #000000; border-top:1px solid #000000; vertical-align:top\">\n<p><strong>Onset of Action</strong></p>\n</td>\n<td style=\"border-bottom:1px solid #000000; border-left:1px solid #000000; border-right:1px solid #000000; border-top:1px solid #000000; vertical-align:top\">\n<ul>\n<li>Has a slower onset (10-15 minutes) compared to faster-acting anesthetics like lidocaine.</li>\n</ul>\n</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td style=\"border-bottom:1px solid #000000; border-left:1px solid #000000; border-right:1px solid #000000; border-top:1px solid #000000; vertical-align:top\">\n<p><strong>Cardiotoxicity</strong></p>\n</td>\n<td style=\"border-bottom:1px solid #000000; border-left:1px solid #000000; border-right:1px solid #000000; border-top:1px solid #000000; vertical-align:top\">\n<ul>\n<li>Major concern with bupivacaine is its potential for cardiotoxicity, especially at higher doses or when inadvertently <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"6a367ebd0c169277719091155a5b0f\">injected</span> intravenously, leading to severe arrhythmias or <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"e1fb96fd2416927771830dfed40e14\">cardiac</span> arrest.</li>\n</ul>\n</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td style=\"border-bottom:1px solid #000000; border-left:1px solid #000000; border-right:1px solid #000000; border-top:1px solid #000000; vertical-align:top\">\n<p><strong>Metabolism</strong></p>\n</td>\n<td style=\"border-bottom:1px solid #000000; border-left:1px solid #000000; border-right:1px solid #000000; border-top:1px solid #000000; vertical-align:top\">\n<ul>\n<li>Metabolized primarily in the liver by <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"29e8e2a5dd16927771855db589c581\">cytochrome</span> P450 enzymes and excreted by the kidneys.</li>\n</ul>\n</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td style=\"border-bottom:1px solid #000000; border-left:1px solid #000000; border-right:1px solid #000000; border-top:1px solid #000000; vertical-align:top\">\n<p><strong>Enantiomers</strong></p>\n</td>\n<td style=\"border-bottom:1px solid #000000; border-left:1px solid #000000; border-right:1px solid #000000; border-top:1px solid #000000; vertical-align:top\">\n<ul>\n<li>The S-enantiomer of bupivacaine, known as levobupivacaine, is associated with <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"10c83adb331692777197f775bec1aa\">reduced</span> <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"5dc2899332169277718350ff2207b9\">cardiotoxicity</span> and is often used as a safer alternative.</li>\n</ul>\n</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td style=\"border-bottom:1px solid #000000; border-left:1px solid #000000; border-right:1px solid #000000; border-top:1px solid #000000; vertical-align:top\">\n<p><strong>Lipid <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"a9295e67a41692777198dce0de3f34\">Solubility</span> & Protein Binding </strong></p>\n</td>\n<td style=\"border-bottom:1px solid #000000; border-left:1px solid #000000; border-right:1px solid #000000; border-top:1px solid #000000; vertical-align:top\">\n<ul>\n<li>Bupivacaine has high <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"a99114a6c216927771916f45ffc66c\">lipid</span> <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"a9295e67a41692777198dce0de3f34\">solubility</span> and high protein binding, which contributes to its prolonged duration of action.</li>\n</ul>\n</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td style=\"border-bottom:1px solid #000000; border-left:1px solid #000000; border-right:1px solid #000000; border-top:1px solid #000000; vertical-align:top\">\n<p><strong>Contraindications</strong></p>\n</td>\n<td style=\"border-bottom:1px solid #000000; border-left:1px solid #000000; border-right:1px solid #000000; border-top:1px solid #000000; vertical-align:top\">\n<ul>\n<li>Should be avoided in patients with severe <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"e1fb96fd2416927771830dfed40e14\">cardiac</span> arrhythmias, and caution should be used in patients with liver disease due to its <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"3268e86ce01692777188f249c64d6e\">hepatic</span> metabolism.</li>\n</ul>\n</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td style=\"border-bottom:1px solid #000000; border-left:1px solid #000000; border-right:1px solid #000000; border-top:1px solid #000000; vertical-align:top\">\n<p><strong>Common Side Effects</strong></p>\n</td>\n<td style=\"border-bottom:1px solid #000000; border-left:1px solid #000000; border-right:1px solid #000000; border-top:1px solid #000000; vertical-align:top\">\n<ul>\n<li>In addition to cardiotoxicity, other potential side effects include <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"e1a4a12fb416927771841c46faf6fb\">CNS</span> toxicity, such as dizziness, seizures, and lightheadedness, especially with <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"fb7ff97e071692777180252299cf10\">accidental</span> <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"837d6227d81692777190a063ea2cd4\">intravascular</span> injection.</li>\n</ul>\n</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td style=\"border-bottom:1px solid #000000; border-left:1px solid #000000; border-right:1px solid #000000; border-top:1px solid #000000; vertical-align:top\">\n<p><strong>Toxicity</strong></p>\n</td>\n<td style=\"border-bottom:1px solid #000000; border-left:1px solid #000000; border-right:1px solid #000000; border-top:1px solid #000000; vertical-align:top\">\n<ul>\n<li>Direct <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"27b78a96071692777190f4dfb93430\">intravenous</span> <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"3509997646169277719014053aa74d\">injection</span> or rapid <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"526ede3fee169277720184378acc5e\">vascular</span> <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"cc20d2d7111692777201fb0caeb3f2\">uptake</span> of the drug is the most common reason for bupivacaine toxicity, which has an upper limit of 2.5 to 3.5 mg/kg upper limit of dosing.</li>\n<li>Treatment for toxicity: 20% intralipid solution.</li>\n</ul>\n</td>\n</tr>\n</tbody>\n\n\n<p style='font-size: 10px; color: #808080; font-style: italic;'></p>",
